				<div class="rightside">

					<h3 data-anchor="alert">Alert</h3>

					<div class="row">
						<p>An alert box with different style and color, based on your need. You can also create your own, it will add the class <em>magma-alert-{alert}</em> to the component, and you can style it the way you want.</p>
						<ul class="attributes">
							<li><strong>alert</strong> Type of alert your want to display.</li>
							<li><strong>animationIn</strong> Animation when the component appears. Default is <em>fadeIn</em>.</li>
							<li><strong>animationOut</strong> Animation when the component disappears. Default is <em>fadeOut</em>.</li>
							<li><strong>isDisplayed</strong> When set to true, the alert is visible.</li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<div class="row">

						<code class="hbs"><pre>
\{{#magma-alert alert="error"}}
  Please enter your firstname
\{{/magma-alert}}

\{{#magma-alert alert="warning"}}
  Are you sure you want to continue?
\{{/magma-alert}}

\{{#magma-alert alert="info"}}
  Have a look to this information, &lt;a href="#"&gt;click here!&lt;/a&gt;
\{{/magma-alert}}

\{{#magma-alert alert="success" animationIn="flipInX" animationOut="flipOutX" isDisplayed=(mut alertIsDisplayed)}}
  Your request has been sent!
\{{/magma-alert}}
						</pre></code>

						<div class="example">

							{{#magma-alert alert="error"}}
								Please enter your firstname
							{{/magma-alert}}

							{{#magma-alert alert="warning"}}
								Are you sure you want to continue?
							{{/magma-alert}}

							{{#magma-alert alert="info"}}
								Have a look to this information, <a href="javascript:alert('Yay!');">click here!</a>
							{{/magma-alert}}

							{{#magma-alert alert="success" animationIn="flipInX" animationOut="flipOutX" isDisplayed=(mut alertIsDisplayed)}}
								Your request has been sent!
							{{/magma-alert}}<br />

							{{#magma-button on-click=(action "toggleAlert")}}Toggle alert visibility{{/magma-button}}
						</div>
					</div>

					<h3 data-anchor="button">Button</h3>

					<div class="row">
						<p>The button is something very important in a web page. If you use the magma theme, you can use the classes <em>magma-small</em> or <em>magma-large</em> to change the size of the component.</p>
						<ul class="attributes">
							<li><strong>disabled</strong> When set to true, the button is disabled, and has the class <em>magma-disabled</em> set to it.</li>
							<li><strong>name</strong> The name is used to share events between the button and the button-group. Only used when part of a button-group.</li>
							<li><strong>pressed</strong> When set to true, the button will have the pressed state.</li>
							<li><strong>on-click</strong> This is the action that will be called whenever the user click on the button.</li>
							<li><strong>value</strong> The value is used to share events between the button and the button-group. Only used when part of a button-group.</li>
						</ul>
					</div>

					<div class="row">

						<h4>Small, default and large</h4>

						<code class="hbs"><pre>
\{{#magma-button class="magma-small" on-click=(action "openAlert")}}
  Bonjour
\{{/magma-button}}

\{{#magma-alert on-click=(action "openAlert")}}
  Bonjour
\{{/magma-alert}}

\{{#magma-alert class="magma-large" on-click=(action "openAlert")}}
  Bonjour
\{{/magma-alert}}
						</pre></code>

						<div class="example">
							{{#magma-button class="magma-small"}}
								Bonjour
							{{/magma-button}}

							{{#magma-button}}
								Bonjour
							{{/magma-button}}

							{{#magma-button class="magma-large"}}
								Bonjour
							{{/magma-button}}
						</div>
					</div>

					<div class="row">

						<h4>Disabled and pressed</h4>

						<code class="hbs"><pre>
\{{#magma-button disabled=true}}
  Bonjour
\{{/magma-button}}

\{{#magma-button pressed=true}}
  Bonjour
\{{/magma-button}}
						</pre></code>

						<div class="example">

							{{#magma-button disabled=true}}
								Bonjour
							{{/magma-button}}

							{{#magma-button pressed=true}}
								Bonjour
							{{/magma-button}}

						</div>
					</div>

					<h3 data-anchor="button-group">Button group</h3>

					<p>You can assemble multiple buttons within a group. They will behave about the same way a radiobutton will work. This is very useful if you want to create a navigation bar for example.</p>
					<ul class="attributes">
						<li><strong>name</strong> This name is mandatory and should be the same in the group and the button itself. It allows to share the events between the two components.</li>
						<li><strong>on-value-change</strong> This is the action that will be called whenever the value of the group changes. The action will receive the value as a parameter.</li>
						<li><strong>value</strong> You can set the value of the current pressed button with this attribute.</li>
					</ul>

					<div class="row">
						<code class="hbs"><pre>
\{{#magma-button-group name="buttonGroupHello" value=(mut buttonGroupInitialValue) on-value-change=(action "buttonGroupValueDidChange")}}
  \{{#magma-button name="buttonGroupHello" value="Bonjour" pressed=true}} Bonjour \{{/magma-button}}
  \{{#magma-button name="buttonGroupHello" value="Hola"}} Hola \{{/magma-button}}
  \{{#magma-button name="buttonGroupHello" value="Hello"}} Hello \{{/magma-button}}
\{{/magma-button-group}}

Selected element: \{{buttonGroupValue}}
						</pre></code>

						<div class="example">
							{{#magma-button-group name="buttonGroupHello" value=(mut buttonGroupInitialValue) on-value-change=(action "buttonGroupValueDidChange")}}
								{{#magma-button name="buttonGroupHello" value="Bonjour" pressed=true}} Bonjour {{/magma-button}}
								{{#magma-button name="buttonGroupHello" value="Hola"}} Hola {{/magma-button}}
								{{#magma-button name="buttonGroupHello" value="Hello"}} Hello {{/magma-button}}
							{{/magma-button-group}}<br />

							Selected element: {{buttonGroupValue}}
						</div>

					</div>

					<h3 data-anchor="checkbox">Checkbox</h3>

					<p>A simple checkbox. You can disable it, make it required or even have an invalid state set on it.</p>
					<ul class="attributes">
						<li><strong>checked</strong> When set to true, the checkbox is ticked.</li>
						<li><strong>disabled</strong> When set to true, the checkbox is disabled, and has the class <em>magma-disabled</em> set to it.</li>
						<li><strong>invalid</strong> When set to true, the checkbox has an invalid state, and has the class <em>magma-invalid</em> set to it.</li>
						<li><strong>name</strong> The name of the checkbox</li>
						<li><strong>required</strong> When set to true, the checkbox has a required state, and has the class <em>magma-required</em> set to it</li>
					</ul>

					<div class="row">
						<code class="hbs"><pre>
\{{magma-checkbox name="checkbox" checked=true}}

Is checked?: \{{checkboxIsChecked}}
						</pre></code>

						<div class="example">
							{{magma-checkbox name="checkbox" checked=checkboxIsChecked}} <br /><br />
							Is checked?: {{checkboxIsChecked}}
						</div>
					</div>

					<h3 data-anchor="form-element">Form element</h3>

					<p>It's not always easy to bind a label to form field with Ember, especially with auto-generated IDs. This will allow you to create a label and to bind it to your input element. You can also create your own label</p>
					<ul class="attributes">
						<li><strong>label</strong> The label to be displayed</li>
					</ul>

					<div class="row">
						<code class="hbs"><pre>
\{{#magma-form-element label="Name:"}}
  \{{magma-textbox value="Alex"}}
\{{/magma-form-element}}

\{{#magma-form-element}}
   \{{magma-checkbox}} &lt;label&gt;I accept the terms and conditions&lt;/label&gt;
\{{/magma-form-element}}
						</pre></code>

						<div class="example">
							{{#magma-form-element label="Name:"}}
								{{magma-textbox value="Alex"}}
							{{/magma-form-element}}

							{{#magma-form-element}}
								{{magma-checkbox}} <label>I accept the terms and conditions</label>
							{{/magma-form-element}}
						</div>
					</div>

					<h3 data-anchor="popover">Popover</h3>

					<div class="row">
						<p>You can create a popover that will appear on top of any element. It can be a tooltip, to display additional information, or you can even use this component to display a list of items (such as a dropdown), or to display a calendar, bound a textbox for example.</p>
						<ul class="attributes">
							<li><strong>animationIn</strong> Animation when the component appears. Default is <em>fadeIn</em>.</li>
							<li><strong>animationOut</strong> Animation when the component disappears. Default is <em>fadeOut</em>.</li>
							<li><strong>for</strong> It corresponds to the ID of the element that will trigger the popover to be displayed or hidden.</li>
							<li><strong>isDisplayed</strong> When set to true, the popover is visible.</li>
							<li><strong>on</strong> By default, the popover will appear on <em>hover</em> the <em>for</em> element, but you can also display it on <em>click</em>.</li>
							<li><strong>on-hide</strong> This is the action that will be called whenever the popover starts to become invisible.</li>
							<li><strong>on-show</strong> This is the action that will be called whenever the popover becomes visible.</li>
							<li><strong>placement</strong> You decide if you want the popover to be display on <em>top</em>, on the <em>left</em>, on the <em>right</em> or at the <em>bottom</em> of the <em>for</em> element.</li>
							<li><strong>alignment</strong> You can align the popover to a side of the <em>for</em> element. When the placement is set to top or bottom, you can align it on the left, the right or center. When the placement is set to left or right, you can align it at the top, the bottom or center.</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="row">
						<code class="hbs"><pre>
\{{#magma-button id="popover-button"}}
  Roll over to display the tooltip
\{{/magma-button}}

\{{#magma-popover for="popover-button" placement="right" alignment="center"}}
  This appears on mouse over
\{{/magma-popover}}

\{{#magma-popover on="click" for="popover-button" placement="bottom" alignment="left"}}
  This appears on click&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
  &lt;img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/69/Ember.js_Logo_and_Mascot.png" width="150"&gt;
\{{/magma-popover}}
						</pre></code>

						<div class="example">
							{{#magma-button id="popover-button" style="background: transparent; border: 1px solid; color: #a31212"}}
								Roll over to display a tooltip. <br />Click to display another one.
							{{/magma-button}}

							{{#magma-popover for="popover-button" on="hover" placement="right" alignment="center"}}
								This appears on mouse over
							{{/magma-popover}}

							{{#magma-popover on="click" for="popover-button" placement="bottom" alignment="left"}}
								This appears on click<br /><br />
								<img src="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/6/69/Ember.js_Logo_and_Mascot.png" width="150">
							{{/magma-popover}}
						</div>
					</div>

					<h3 data-anchor="progress">Progress</h3>

					<p>This creates a progress bar, very useful to display the state of something loading. You can display the value of the progression as well. You can access the property <em>indicatorValue</em> which returns the percentage of progression.</p>
					<ul class="attributes">
						<li><strong>indicatorAnimation</strong> When set to true, the progress bar will be animated. Default is <em>true</em>.</li>
						<li><strong>indicatorAnimationDuration</strong> When <em>indicatorAnimation</em> is set to true, this will set the speed of the <em>indicatorValue</em> animation in miliseconds. Default is <em>400</em>.</li>
						<li><strong>max</strong> The maximum value the progress bar can reach. Default is <em>100</em>.</li>
						<li><strong>value</strong> The current value of the progress bar. Default is <em>0</em>.</li>
					</ul>

					<div class="row">
						<code class="hbs"><pre>
\{{magma-progress value=50}}

\{{#magma-progress value=progressValue as |progress|}}
  \{{progress.indicatorValue}}%
\{{/magma-popover}}
						</pre></code>

						<div class="example">

							{{magma-progress value=50}}

							{{#magma-progress value=progressValue as |progress|}}
								{{progress.indicatorValue}}%
							{{/magma-progress}}<br />

							{{#magma-button on-click=(action "changeProgressValue")}}Change progress value{{/magma-button}}

						</div>
					</div>

					<h3 data-anchor="radiobutton">Radiobutton</h3>

					<p>A simple radiobutton. You can disable it, make it required or even have an invalid state set on it.</p>
					<ul class="attributes">
						<li><strong>checked</strong> When set to true, the radiobutton is ticked</li>
						<li><strong>disabled</strong>  When set to true, the radiobutton is disabled, and has the class <em>magma-disabled</em> set to it.</li>
						<li><strong>invalid</strong> When set to true, the checkbox has an invalid state, and has the class <em>magma-invalid</em> set to it.</li>
						<li><strong>name</strong> The name of the checkbox</li>
						<li><strong>required</strong> When set to true, the checkbox has a required state, and has the class <em>magma-required</em> set to it</li>
						<li><strong>value</strong> Value of the radiobutton.</li>
					</ul>

					<div class="row">
						<code class="hbs"><pre>
\{{magma-radiobutton name="radiobuttonGroup" value="Hello"}}
						</pre></code>

						<div class="example">
							{{magma-radiobutton name="radiobuttonGroup1" value="Hello"}}
						</div>
					</div>

					<h3 data-anchor="radiobutton-group">Radio button group</h3>

					<p>A radiobutton doesn't work alone, they work in group. With this component, you can get the value of the current selected radiobutton.</p>
					<ul class="attributes">
						<li><strong>name</strong> This name is mandatory and should be the same in the group and the button itself. It allows to share the events between the two components.</li>
						<li><strong>on-value-change</strong> This is the action that will be called whenever the value of the group changes. The action will receive the value as a parameter.</li>
						<li><strong>value</strong> You can get the value of the current pressed button within this attribute. You can also set the default value.</li>
					</ul>

					<div class="row">
						<code class="hbs"><pre>
\{{magma-radiobutton-group name="radiobuttonHelloGroup" value=(mut radiobuttonGroupInitialValue) on-value-change=(action "radiobuttonGroupValueDidChange")}}
  \{{magma-radiobutton name="radiobuttonHelloGroup" value="Bonjour"}}
  \{{magma-radiobutton name="radiobuttonHelloGroup" value="Hola"}}
  \{{magma-radiobutton name="radiobuttonHelloGroup" value="Hello"}}
\{{/magma-radiobutton-group}}

Selected element: \{{radiobuttonGroupValue}}
						</pre></code>

						<div class="example">
							{{#magma-radiobutton-group name="radiobuttonHelloGroup" value=(mut radiobuttonGroupInitialValue) on-value-change=(action "radiobuttonGroupValueDidChange")}}
								{{magma-radiobutton name="radiobuttonHelloGroup" value="Bonjour" checked=true}}
								{{magma-radiobutton name="radiobuttonHelloGroup" value="Hola"}}
								{{magma-radiobutton name="radiobuttonHelloGroup" value="Hello"}}
							{{/magma-radiobutton-group}}<br />

							Selected element: {{radiobuttonGroupValue}}
						</div>
					</div>

					<h3 data-anchor="range">Range</h3>

					<p>Creates a slider where you can set a minimum, current and maximum value.</p>
					<ul class="attributes">
						<li><strong>disabled</strong>  When set to true, the range has a disabled state, and has the class <em>magma-disabled</em> set to it.</li>
						<li><strong>max</strong> Indicate the maximum value of the allowed range of values for the element.</li>
						<li><strong>min</strong> Indicate the minimum value of the allowed range of values for the element. </li>
						<li><strong>step</strong> Specifies the value granularity of the elementâ€™s value.</li>
						<li><strong>value</strong> Current value.</li>
					</ul>

					<div class="row">
						<code class="hbs"><pre>
\{{magma-range value=rangeValue}}
\{{magma-range value=rangeValue disabled=true}}
						</pre></code>

						<div class="example">
							{{magma-range value=rangeValue}}<br />
							{{magma-range value=rangeValue disabled=true}}<br />
							<br />

							Selected value: {{rangeValue}}
						</div>
					</div>

					<h3 data-anchor="selectbox">Selectbox</h3>

					<p>Creates a drop-down list using the select tag. If you use the magma theme, you can use the classes <em>magma-small</em> or <em>magma-large</em> to change the size of the component.</p>
					<ul class="attributes">
						<li><strong>action</strong> You can call an action when the drop-down did change. It will have the <em>selection</em> in parameter.</li>
						<li><strong>content</strong> An array containing objects to be displayed in the drop-down.</li>
						<li><strong>disabled</strong>  When set to true, the selectbox has a disabled state, and has the class <em>magma-disabled</em> set to it.</li>
						<li><strong>invalid</strong> When set to true, the selectbox has an invalid state, and has the class <em>magma-invalid</em> set to it.</li>
						<li><strong>prompt</strong> You can define a first item to be displayed when there is no selection.</li>
						<li><strong>optionLabelPath</strong> It specifies the path on each object to the desired property for the element's text.</li>
						<li><strong>optionValuePath</strong> Option is used to specify the path on each object to the desired property for the value attribute.</li>
						<li><strong>required</strong> When set to true, the selectbox has a required state, and has the class <em>magma-required</em> set to it.</li>
						<li><strong>selection</strong> This contains the currently selected object in the drop-down. It can be set with the item to display.</li>
